verbose_text: The hearing recovery rate in patients with initial hearing loss of 40-90 dB (moderate) was significantly lower in children than in adults (62.5% vs. 82.8%, P = 0.001), whereas the hearing recovery rate in patients with initial hearing loss> 90 dB (profound) was significantly higher in children than in adults (60.0% vs. 45.4%, P = 0.010).
